# Atlas Universalis Project Rules

You are working on **Atlas Universalis**, a multi-application platform consisting of:
- **Main Site** (`atlasuniversalis.com`) — Portfolio/landing page
- **QuickPRO/AtlasOps** (`quickpro.atlasuniversalis.com`) — AI job application platform
- **AtlasForge** (`playground.atlasuniversalis.com`) — UI component playground
- **Browser Extension** — Job posting capture

## Required Skills

Read these skills when working on relevant areas:

| Skill | Location | Use When |
|-------|----------|----------|
| atl | `.cursor/skills/atl/SKILL.md` | General platform development |
| atlasops | `.cursor/skills/atlasops/SKILL.md` | Backend/API work |
| version-logger | `.cursor/skills/version-logger/SKILL.md` | After ANY changes (required) |

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy (async), PostgreSQL, Celery + Redis
- **Frontend**: Vue 3 + Vite, Tailwind CSS, Pinia
- **Deployment**: DigitalOcean droplet, Nginx, GitHub Actions

## Non-Negotiables

1. **Never hardcode secrets** — Use environment variables
2. **Never break existing routes** — `/` and `/pages/{slug}` must work
3. **Always log changes** — Invoke version-logger after completing work
4. **Prefer async** — Use async patterns throughout the stack
